The Attachments Macro should be improved by allowing a default sort order to be specified in the macro.  In our specific use-case, the default of descending date sort is great, but we also have some use cases where ascending would be preferred. 

The first comment on CONF-8151 (https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/CONF-8151?focusedCommentId=77139&page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-77139) makes it seem that ordering can be specified, however when using the example in that comment and replacing "desc" with "asc" or "ascend" or "ascending" the sort order is still descending by date.

Implementation of this feature could simply be to allow the behavior suggested in that comment:
{attachments:sortBy=date/asc} 

Or perhaps:
{attachments:sortBy=date|order=asc} 

I would also suggest that the macro allow for users to specify order as any of: "asc" "ascend" "ascending" "desc" "descend" "descending" -- but with the markup editor going away in 4.0, I don't know whether this would be necessary or appropriate.

