As of 3.5.6, Confluence can currently only migrate directories from Confluence 3.4.x and below as "Generic LDAP" or "Microsoft Active Directory". Users who are using RFC2307 based LDAP directories will not have their directories migrated correctly.

These users usually have {{useUnqualifiedUsernameForMembershipComparison}} set to true in their {{atlassian-user.xml}} file. I.e. their membership attribute only contains usernames, and not full DNs. Confluence should look for that attribute and migrate such directories as "Generic Posix/RFC2307 Directory".

