Right now, Confluence serves all actions, attachments and thumbnails from the same URL whether a user is logged in or not. This means that all responses for most attachments and RSS feeds include the following Cache-Control and Expires headers:
{noformat}
Cache-Control: private, must-revalidate, max-age=600.
Expires: Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 GMT.
{noformat}

All other actions have the headers:
{noformat}
Cache-Control: no-cache, must-revalidate.
Expires: Thu, 01 Jan 1970 00:00:00 GMT.
{noformat}

For anonymous users, there is no reason to mark the content as private. Instead, Confluence should serve anonymous content from a distinct URL with less restrictive caching headers, so that proxies between the browser and Confluence can reduce the load on Confluence for public, unchanged content.

